---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';

const lang = 'en';
const pathname = Astro.url.pathname;
const updated = '2026-05-14';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Use - Arcanesys" lang={lang} description="Terms of use for arcanesys.fr. Licensing (MIT/AGPL), honest maturity disclosure, liability disclaimer. Governed by French law.">
  <PageHeader
    lang={lang}
    pathname={pathname}
    titleKey="pageHeader.terms.title"
    subtitleKey="pageHeader.terms.subtitle"
  />

  <article class="prose max-w-prose mx-auto px-10 py-12">
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> {updated}</p>

    <h2><span class="num">01</span>What this site is</h2>
    <p>
      This site (arcanesys.fr) presents the NixFleet framework and its commercial wrap. It
      links to source repositories on GitHub, technical documentation, and a contact form for
      pilot inquiries. It is provided as informational material.
    </p>

    <h2><span class="num">02</span>Licensing of the software</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>nixfleet</strong> framework + agent: MIT license</li>
      <li><strong>nixfleet</strong> control plane: AGPL-3.0</li>
      <li><strong>nixfleet-compliance</strong>: MIT license</li>
      <li><strong>nixfleet-demo</strong>: MIT license</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Each repository's <code>LICENSE</code> file is the authoritative source. By using the
      software, you accept the relevant licenses.
    </p>

    <h2><span class="num">03</span>Honest maturity disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      NixFleet is tested with 14 end-to-end fleet-harness scenarios and 72 Rust test files.
      The signed-artifact chain has been exercised on operator hardware. <strong>It is not
      yet certified for sovereign deployments</strong> (no SecNumCloud, no ANSSI
      qualification at this date. See <a href={`/${lang}/vision/`}>Vision</a> for the
      trajectory). Pilot operators run NixFleet on pre-production or non-critical production
      hosts. Production deployment to critical systems should follow a successful pilot.
    </p>

    <h2><span class="num">04</span>Pilot offer</h2>
    <p>
      Pilots are free of charge, governed by a separate written agreement (the Pilot SOW)
      executed between Arcanesys and the operator's legal entity. The full conditions of a
      pilot are detailed at <a href={`/${lang}/pilot/`}>/pilot</a> and in the SOW. They
      override any informational content on this site.
    </p>

    <h2><span class="num">05</span>Liability disclaimer</h2>
    <p>
      The software is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind, as stated in the
      respective MIT and AGPL licenses. Nothing on this site constitutes legal or compliance
      advice. Consult your qualified counsel or compliance officer for binding regulatory
      interpretation (NIS2, DORA, ISO 27001, ANSSI BP-028, etc.).
    </p>
    <p>
      Within the limits of applicable EU consumer protection law, Arcanesys's total liability
      arising from informational content on this site is limited to the amount paid by the
      visitor (zero for the public site). Commercial relationships are governed by the
      relevant contracts (pilot SOW, support agreement, license agreement).
    </p>

    <h2><span class="num">06</span>Third-party trademarks and external links</h2>
    <p>
      NixOS is a trademark of the NixOS Foundation. Other trademarks are property of their
      respective owners. External links are provided for convenience; Arcanesys is not
      responsible for the content of external sites.
    </p>

    <h2><span class="num">07</span>Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by French law. Disputes that cannot be resolved amicably fall
      under the jurisdiction of the competent courts of the operator's registered office in
      France.
    </p>

    <h2><span class="num">08</span>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:contact@arcanesys.fr">contact@arcanesys.fr</a>.
    </p>
  </article>

  <Footer lang={lang} />
</Layout>
